title: 820-00165 no power
message:
Liquid damage minimal - R5117, replaced.

Inspected board at 45x, no signs of further liquid damage.

PPBUS = 8.6
3V42 = 3V42
S5 rails = 3V3 and 5V

SMC_ADAPTER_EN = 3V3
PM_SLP_S5 = 0V
PM_SLP_S4 = 0V

No power cycles

Any thoughts please?

UPDATE: Replaced R1451 PM_DSW_PWRGD.
Now fan spins up for 10 seconds and then off. Connected a fully charged working battery to check for USB initialization but nothing. all_sys_pwrgd goes high while fan spins.
Also powers on from battery in the same way but no mouse LED. CPU does get hot.

title: 820-00165 no power
message: CPU Vcore present I assume? This could really be anything, corrosion under SMC or something stupid.
